Day 29 ‚úîÔ∏è Today I'm part of the midnight Yogi crew who are getting their flow on after 12AM in the comments! Haha! So it also happens to be Bruce Lee's birthday today (or was like an hour ago), and one of his teachings I always enjoy is to "be like water." An example of this today would be that I got invited to one of my friend's work parties for Thanksgiving. It's been a while since I've socialized with so many people, and it was pleasant: but so draining! By the time I got home, changed and rolled out the mat, my body was begging for a short nap. Just rolling around in the floor released so many joints and muscles, and I just needed some time to rest. I didn't realize how socializing can be draining fire time and efficient. But my system is fried, and needs sleep. I think I'm just going to ramble on unless I get some sleep, so much love to you all, start empowering yourself with good gear.

Approaching the end of the my first 30 days, I had some time to reflect this morning.
I have really enjoyed this practice so much more than I expected. I usually prefer group fitness activities, but I realized that it's because I am so competitive. I use other to motivate me to work harder, go longer, etc. I've had some health issues and right now I can't do the kinds of workouts and activities that I typically enjoy.
So, I came to this practice hoping to begin to heal my body outside of western medicine. It's really been healing my mind. And I found that doing this alone, at home, has really freed me and given me permission to both embrace the challenges and celebrate my own progress without comparing myself to others.
